    {
        "content": "<p>For your last statement, it should not mention <code>differentiable_on</code> but <code>diffContOnCl</code>. So, something like <code>circleAverage_re_smul_of_diffContOnCl</code>. Keep only in the theorem the main features of the lemma to distinguish between them. For me, the main point of the version you've written is that you're using a real part, so that's what I've kept in the name. Since you're writing the different versions, you know why you need them and what's important in them, so that's what you should mention in the name.</p>",
        "id": 573227802,
